<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-462-586  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 462 586.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>M.D. Computing  May-June 1989 v6 n3 p167(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>X-File: a program for maintaining a radiographic teaching file.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Markivee, Carroll R.; Chenoweth, Jeffrey L.; Abbas, Syed A.;andO;Patel, Bhargavi K.; Savci, Suheyla F.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>X-File is a program designed for entry, retrieval, and maintenanceof radiographic case-file data on a personal computer.andP;  It offersconsiderable assistance in keeping records straight in a radiologydepartment.andP;  The case files are based on the Index for RoentgenDiagnoses.andP;  The terms and code numbers of the index are built intothe software, so the user only needs to enter the diagnostic termthat is wanted, the code numbers and exact terminology areassigned automatically.andP;  The program has been in use for two yearsat the Department of Radiology at the St. Louis University MedicalCenter.andP;  The system can hold over 70,000 entries on a 20-megabytehard disk.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     St. Louis UniversityMedical Advice SystemsRadiologyApplicationsTeaching.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>